This is a problem with the template generation mechanism. If the template is
newer than the class file, a new class file with an incremented index is
generated and used. 
What was broken was the creating of the source with the incremented index. Due
to bug 95680 being fixed by EMF, we now have an extra static method - 
------------------------------------------------
public class <className> implemnets ITemplate{
...
  public static synchronized <className>create(String lineSeparator)
  {
    nl = lineSeparator;
    <className>result = new <className>();
    nl = null;
    return result;
  }
----------------------------

The index was being incremented on the class declaration, but not in the static
create method's return and variable declaration. Releasing class
JavaObjectEmitter to fix this, and TemplateObjectFactoryTest to enable the test.
